'''Elias Saad''' ({{langx|ar|إِلْيَاس سَعْد}}; born 27 December 1999) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[left winger]] for {{German football updater|Hannover}} club [[Hannover 96]] on loan from [[FC Augsburg]]. Born in Germany, he plays for the [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia national team]], having previously been a former international for the [[Germany national futsal team]].

==Club career==
From [[Wilhelmsburg, Hamburg]], in 2017 Saad played under-19 football for [[Buxtehuder SV]].<ref name="schneider">{{cite news |last1=Schneider |first1=Mirko |title=Eintracht Norderstedt: Flügelflitzer Elias Saad will Profi werden|trans-title=Eintracht Norderstedt: Winger Elias Saad wants to become a professional |url=https://www.abendblatt.de/region/norderstedt/sport_135/article236423145/Fluegelflitzer-Elias-Saad-will-Fussball-Profi-werden.html |access-date=9 May 2023 |work=Hamburger Abendblatt |date=13 September 2022 |language=German}}</ref> In 2019 he joined [[Futsal Bundesliga]] team [[Hamburg Panthers]]<ref>{{cite news |title=Personelle Lage bei Sparta Futsal HSC entspannt sich |trans-title=Personnel situation at Sparta Futsal HSC relaxes |url=https://www.abendblatt.de/hamburg/harburg/sport/article227311847/Personelle-Lage-bei-Sparta-Futsal-HSC-entspannt-sich.html |access-date=9 May 2023 |work=Hamburger Abendblatt |date=8 October 2019 |language=German}}</ref> and became the youngest player to make an appearance for the [[Germany national futsal team]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hardt |first1=Andreas |title=Futsal und Amateure: Wie Elias Saad zum Durchstarter wurde |trans-title=Futsal and amateurs: How Elias Saad became a high-flyer |url=https://www.abendblatt.de/sport/fussball/st-pauli/article238346243/Futsal-und-Amateure-Wie-Elias-Saad-zum-Durchstarter-wurde.html |access-date=9 May 2023 |work=Hamburger Abendblatt |date=9 May 2023 |language=German}}</ref> He also played football for [[HSV Barmbek-Uhlenhorst]] in the fifth-tier [[Oberliga Hamburg]], making 29 appearances in which he scored eleven goals and was credited with seven assists.<ref name="schneider"/> Whilst playing amateur football in Hamburg Saad also trained as a wholesale and retail salesman.<ref name="schneider"/><ref>{{cite news |last1=Bode |first1=Hanno |title=Unverhofft kommt oft: Wie Elias Saad Profi beim FC St. Pauli wurde |trans-title=The unexpected often happens: How Elias Saad became a professional at FC St. Pauli |url=https://www.ndr.de/sport/fussball/Unverhofft-kommt-oft-Wie-Elias-Saad-Profi-beim-FC-St-Pauli-wurde,pauli7230.html |access-date=9 May 2023 |work=NDR |date=4 January 2023 |language=German}}</ref> In March 2021 Saad agreed to join [[Regionalliga Nord]] side [[FC Eintracht Norderstedt 03]], signing a two-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Heiden |first1=Niklas |title=Deal fix: Elias Saad stürmt ab Sommer für Norderstedt |trans-title=Deal fixed: Elias Saad to play for Norderstedt in summer |url=https://www.amateur-fussball-hamburg.de/deal-fix-elias-saad-stuermt-ab-sommer-fuer-norderstedt/ |website=Amateur Fußball Hamburg |access-date=9 May 2023 |language=German |date=16 March 2021}}</ref>

On 1 December 2022, Saad was announced as signing for [[2. Bundesliga]] side [[FC St. Pauli]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fcstpauli.com/news/fc-st-pauli-verpflichtet-sturmer-elias-saad/|title=Der FC St. Pauli verpflichtet Stürmer Elias Saad|trans-title=FC St. Pauli signs forward Elias Saad|access-date=9 May 2023 |date=1 December 2022|website=FC St. Pauli}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Mey |first1=Christopher |title=Von Eintracht Norderstedt zum FC St. Pauli: Der Wechsel von Elias Saad |trans-title=From Eintracht Norderstedt to FC St. Pauli: The transfer of Elias Saad |url=https://www.abendblatt.de/region/norderstedt/sport_135/article237049817/Transferueberraschung-So-kam-Elias-Saad-zum-FC-St-Pauli.html |access-date=9 May 2023 |work=Hamburger Abendblatt |date=1 December 2022 |language=German}}</ref> He made his debut in the 2. Bundesliga for St. Pauli as a substitute against [[Eintracht Braunschweig]] on 16 April 2023.<ref name="wolff">{{cite news |last1=Wolff |first1=Sebastian |title=Saad ist St. Paulis Derby-Gewinner |trans-title=Saad is St Pauli's derby winner |url=https://www.kicker.de/saad-ist-st-paulis-derby-gewinner-948308/artikel |access-date=9 May 2023 |work=kicker |date=24 April 2023 |language=German}}</ref> He scored his first league goal for the club the following week in the derby game against Hamburger SV.<ref name="wolff"/> The following week he made his first league start for St. Pauli, at home against [[Arminia Bielefeld]] on 30 April 2023.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Weber |first1=Nils |title=Saads Startelf-Debüt bei St. Pauli: Mächtig Wirbel, viel Applaus |trans-title=Saad's starting eleven debut for St. Pauli: A lot of commotion, a lot of applause |url=https://www.mopo.de/sport/fc-st-pauli/maechtig-wirbel-saad-startet-bei-startelf-debuet-durch-und-findet-es-ganz-okay/ |access-date=9 May 2023 |work=MOPO |date=30 April 2023 |language=German}}</ref>

On 26 June 2025, Saad signed a four-year contract with [[FC Augsburg]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=FC Augsburg|url=https://www.fcaugsburg.de/en/article/fca-complete-the-signing-of-elias-saad-22142|title=FCA complete the signing of Elias Saad|date=26 June 2025|access-date=1 July 2025}}</ref> On 14 January 2026, he was loaned by [[Hannover 96]] in [[2. Bundesliga]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Hannover 96|url=https://www.hannover96.de/newscenter/news/details/new6967551c3ce25425363149-aus-der-bundesliga-in-die-96-offensive-hannover-96-leiht-elias-saad-vom-fc-augsburg.html|title=Hannover 96 leiht Elias Saad vom FC Augsburg|trans-title=Hannover 96 loan Elias Saad from FC Augsburg|date=14 January 2026|access-date=14 January 2026|language=de}}</ref>

==International career==
In August 2023 Saad received his first call-up to the [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia national team]].<ref>{{cite web |title=St. Paulis Saad lebt seinen Traum |trans-title=St Pauli's Saad lives his dream |url=https://www.kicker.de/st-paulis-saad-lebt-seinen-traum-967031/artikel |website=kicker |access-date=4 September 2023 |language=German |date=4 September 2023}}</ref>

He made his debut on 26 March 2024 in a friendly against New Zealand.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/701262/tunisia-new-zealand|title=Tunisia v New Zealand game report|date=26 March 2024}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Born in Germany, Saad is of Tunisian descent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ettachkila.com/football-interview-elias-saad-jouer-pour-la-tunisie-sera-une-fierte/|title=Football, Interview Elias Saad : " Jouer pour la Tunisie sera une fierté. " – Ettachkila}}</ref>

